{"name":"Sanguine Rite","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/wounds/blood-spurt-spray-red.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor can cut herself to harness the power of her own blood to fuel her magical abilities. When casting any spell, she can reduce the MP cost of that spell by 1 at the price of 1 HP. This talent can only be used when casting a spell, and cannot be used to stockpile MP. Further, only 1 HP can converted into 1 MP per casting, not more.</p>","purchaseCost":10,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gylUVJjrtNU3Va3A"}},"_id":"0DZSrrchoYum1olI"}
{"name":"Outlander","type":"talent","img":"icons/creatures/magical/humanoid-silhouette-glowing-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is versed in dealing with strange entities, thanks to her upbringing and life experience. For a social skill check (e.g. Charm, Deception, Menace, or Performance) against monsters, spirits, undead, and any type of creature that is neither natural beast nor sapient mortal, convert a single miss into 1 hit. This talent may not be used more than once against the same individual, and can only be used once against an organization targeted by social networking during downtime.&nbsp;</p>","purchaseCost":10,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EEdrZAvGSM5JLqIp"}},"_id":"1dwjXPVpv2eZA49j"}
{"name":"Dragon Breath","type":"talent","img":"icons/consumables/potions/bottle-round-label-cork-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor can drink the contents of an acid bomb or fire bomb and belch either flames or poisonous gas, somehow without dying. This attack is identical to the standard use of a bomb (i.e. same damage, effects, and close area of effect), except that it only strikes up to short range and uses the Alchemy skill for attack rolls.</p>","purchaseCost":10,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RlwRMD2LzRZeVYeb"}},"_id":"1orzMEZNgMNL9fkv"}
{"name":"Chemical Warfare","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/toxins/bottle-open-vapors-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor's secret stash of experimental concoctions comes out to weaken armor, torment with pain, or cause her target to slip onto the ground. She may burn 3 MP <em>before</em> making a melee or missile (but not magic) attack for the potential to do more damage. If her attack is successful, she makes an Alchemy skill check with the same task difficulty as her attack roll and adds each hit to the damage.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EjcCCUhlQsrcCI6U"}},"_id":"2L6nYHdBt1lJkwl3"}
{"name":"Pet Sortie","type":"talent","img":"icons/creatures/claws/claw-bear-paw-swipe-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor who has a familiar (i.e. has the Whisperer talent) can use her action to sic her familiar on a target. This attack is considered a melee attack (defended against with either Dodge or Parry) but it can strike any target up to medium range away from the familiar's person. She makes a Beast Ken skill check against her target&rsquo;s defense, scoring 1 damage per hit rolled. For each subsequent turn after launching a pet sortie, the actor can choose to have her familiar press the attack (making another Beast Ken skill check to harm the target) by either using her action this way or burning 3 MP.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.o4QQymVCxkym6tYr"}},"_id":"2ZJy38U9qEeUaCJ2"}
{"name":"Adept","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/symbols/chevron-elipse-circle-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is able to channel her magical reserves to improve her mundane abilities. Before making <em>any </em>skill check, she can burn 2 MP to convert 1 fate die into an attribute die and do this as many times as her MP reserves allow.</p>","purchaseCost":35,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XScdB8GwXWur7HrA"}},"_id":"2ZKp4cWeEJMtlCJx"}
{"name":"Bottled Magic","type":"talent","img":"icons/consumables/potions/bottle-corked-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor can cast a cantrip into an alchemical vial which can be imbibed later to experience the effects of the cantrip. This talent can bottle the following cantrips: Astral Eyes, Babel, Beacon Blade, Beckoner, Bloom Blessing, Conjured Closet, Dissemble, Scout Sprite, Share Sight, Swarm Song, and Transporter. To bottle a cantrip, she simply burns the MP required to cast it plus an additional 2 MP. She must know a cantrip to bottle it, but <em>anyone </em>who imbibes this bottled cantrip benefits from it.</p>","purchaseCost":40,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AK5z5bFTtdANcp8l"}},"_id":"2e1HXklvIjaN34hO"}
{"name":"Reaper","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/death/weapon-scythe-rune-green.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is skilled at fighting multiple threats at once. To do so, she can instead use the &ldquo;skill checks vs. groups&rdquo; mechanic to strike at every target that is close to her (including her allies). Note: each target still gets to declare their defense before the roll is made.</p>","purchaseCost":50,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NW6zFsvU5C8usNQf"}},"_id":"2uAEaGIoxxNfh3kd"}
{"name":"Demolitionist","type":"talent","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/bomb-fuse-black-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is extremely adept at making bombs and can shape and deploy them in ways that other alchemists cannot. As a free downtime action, she can turn a fire bomb or acid bomb into 2 fire or 2 acid arrows/bolts. These missiles hit like normal arrows/bolts, but also add either the fire or acid effects to the target. Also as a free downtime action, she can fuse bombs of the same type together to create a single bomb with a short area of effect instead of close area of effect.</p>","purchaseCost":20,"tiered":false,"tiers":3,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oSdMepH0w5Ucx23C"}},"_id":"3jfT8N5tLQfMywxw"}
{"name":"Battle Buddy","type":"talent","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-marked-green.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor who has a familiar (i.e. has the Whisperer talent) is protected by it when she's unconscious. While incapacitated during combat, she makes a Beast Ken skill check against any threat of her choice, scoring 1 damage per hit rolled. This attack is considered a melee attack (defended against with either Dodge or Parry) but it can strike any target up to medium range away from the familiar's person.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zeTs4MkKizXtrvM7"}},"_id":"4aCKO8w7zAMWv85v"}
{"name":"Tower","type":"talent","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-segmented-purple.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor has trained extensively with using a shield. She gains +1 DR when she uses a shield in conjunction with the Parry defense against an incoming melee or missile attack.</p>","purchaseCost":20,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.z85LP950cb5BlsmS"}},"_id":"4nQDiisMdhyJ8xtG"}
{"name":"Death Spiral","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/movement/ball-spinning-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is skilled at using aerial maneuvers and tumbling to make strikes that are difficulty to anticipate or avoid. She may burn 3 MP<em> before</em> making a melee or missile (but not magic) attack for the potential to do more damage. If her attack is successful, she makes an Acrobatics skill check with the same task difficulty as her attack roll and adds each hit to the damage.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XqDJjWk51Nc51Sb3"}},"_id":"6b6MOGQlb7yDveKE"}
{"name":"Highborn","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is versed in dealing with \"polite society,\" thanks to her upbringing and life experience. For a social skill check (e.g. Charm, Deception, Menace, or Performance) made against a target from \"polite society\" (e.g. nobles, courtiers, knights, and the gentry, etc.), convert a single miss into 1 hit. This talent may not be used more than once against the same individual.</p>","purchaseCost":10,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Mh0pb7OHtzaQcZ4K"}},"_id":"6zGZ9mgP3ZhXrF3C"}
{"name":"Exploiter","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/targeting/crosshair-pointed-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor has such an eye for detail that she can intuit the weaknesses of her foes. She may burn 3 MP <em>before</em> making a melee or missile (but not magic) attack for the potential to do more damage. If her attack is successful, she makes a Scrounge skill check with the same task difficulty as her attack roll and adds each hit to the damage.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.nqO7mgEUunCZR0MN"}},"_id":"87mnT7vttN0k3GWY"}
{"name":"Counter-Scry","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/perception/orb-eye-scrying.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor can intuitively sense when she is being observed through magical means. The GM must inform this actor's player whenever she triggers an Alarm Glyph or is being observed via Share Sight, Shard Scry, or Uncanny Eye. Other than sensing this phenomenon is occurring, she is provided no other information.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bb1hQZwvlyRXGYYF"}},"_id":"8P3EQTPhN7CAAsUn"}
{"name":"Unkillable","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/lightning/barrier-shield-orb-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor can take an unusual amount of punishment before becoming incapacitated. Her max HP increases by 1 point. This talent may be purchased multiple times, though its UP cost doubles after an actor reaches 20 HP.</p>","purchaseCost":10,"tiered":true,"tiers":10,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vFGaXcrVLaLL6p8L"}},"_id":"9PdF0EfL9xus7SQS"}
{"name":"Ground Game","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-poison-dripping-green.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is especially brutal while in a grapple. When she makes an attack against a threat she is grappling with, her unarmed attacks or attacks using &ldquo;dirty&rdquo; weapons have their damage upgraded by 1. This talent can be purchased up to 3 times. Yes, this stacks with those other damage talents you have (e.g. Bloodletter, Striker, etc.).</p>","purchaseCost":20,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FZ37taX47aK0zkCm"}},"_id":"AhTZ4A412r5MG951"}
{"name":"Codebreaker","type":"talent","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor spends much of her spare time scouring books, scrolls, town boards, code engines, and registries for keyphrase material. There is a 10% chance that she&rsquo;ll just happen to know the keyphrase to any instance of symmetric cryptomancy she encounters, no matter how complex it is.</p>","purchaseCost":15,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.g0stBuEnslN7Vss6"}},"_id":"Ap3OQeJvErLpeKTC"}
{"name":"Cling to Life","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-hand-gold-green-light.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor simply refuses to die. When she loses 1 HP from a mortal wound or dying status, she can instead choose to lose 2 MP. Obviously, this can only last as long as her MP reserves allow.</p>","purchaseCost":15,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Fpu0VNN2MDc6kRxY"}},"_id":"BRaACBSJm2Q830F7"}
{"name":"Astral Camouflage","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is so adept at casting a particular spell that she can do so without emitting magical residue from her person. Choose a single spell from the following list: Blink, Conjured Closet, Dead Host, or Glamour. When she casts this spell, the spell's magical residue cannot be seen by someone who has cast the Astral Eyes cantrip.</p>","purchaseCost":15,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HeusVDw7EktvQnba"}},"_id":"BXriVmENRQCKNvpW"}
{"name":"Skill Break","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-flight-wings-runes-red-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is especially good at a skill because of a natural gift she has. When making skill checks with this skill, you can convert 1 botch (and only 1 botch) into 1 hit. When selecting this talent, designate a single skill it applies to (e.g. Charm) and invent a natural gift providing this advantage (e.g. Attractive). Document this in the &ldquo;talents and spells&rdquo; section of the character sheet (e.g. &ldquo;Skill Break: Charm - Attractive) but also fill in the &ldquo;1&rdquo; Talent Marker next to the appropriate skill. This talent may be selected multiple times.</p>\n<p>A &ldquo;natural gift&rdquo; is something inherent to an actor, not something developed through experience. Here are some examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tracking - Honed Senses</li>\n<li>Scrounge - Eye for Detail</li>\n<li>Deception - Silver Tongue</li>\n<li>Sleight of Hand - Innocent Demeanor</li>\n<li>Query - Inquisitive Mind</li>\n<li>Craft - Patience</li>\n<li>Fired Missile - Deadeye</li>\n<li>Alchemy - Green Thumb</li>\n<li>Feat of Strength - Massive Frame</li>\n<li>Beast Ken - Killer Instincts</li>\n<li>Brute Melee - Strong Arm</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It is also perfectly fine to reuse the same natural gift for multiple Skill Breaks (e.g. Silver Tongue can apply to both Charm and Deception). While designating a Skill Break&rsquo;s natural gift has no impact on game mechanics, it is something you can and should incorporate into the narrative.</p>\n<p>When selected for either Endurance or Willpower, the cost of this talent is doubled.</p>","purchaseCost":25,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pZY4iLJFdI6TdlzB"}},"_id":"BnCwcQxXr8nmcYWn"}
{"name":"Soma Head","type":"talent","img":"icons/consumables/drinks/coconut-fruit-milk.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is able to shrug off the effects of soma addiction. The Willpower skill check to remain productive during downtime despite pure soma addiction is reduced from tough to challenging. For soma rock, it is reduced from challenging to trivial. For soma leaf, addiction has no effect.</p>","purchaseCost":15,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wHURYjZckNktvQcT"}},"_id":"Da9VUmvVSfyi64qV"}
{"name":"Sniper","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/targeting/crosshair-scope-sniper-green.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor&rsquo;s aim with ranged weapons is especially accurate, striking targets&rsquo; most vulnerable points, upgrading the damage of both Fired Missile and Thrown Missile attacks by 1. This talent can be purchased up to 3 times.</p>","purchaseCost":25,"tiered":true,"tiers":3,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eTwFcKxjM72qwQcR"}},"_id":"Dv4DPJ9DE8iZKFSN"}
{"name":"Daggerist","type":"talent","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-engraved-black.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor has learned the dagger techniques of the dwarven Cloak, which requires wielding a dagger with two hands like it was a claymore. This is a tiered talent that gets stronger every time it is purchased.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I) Deflector - A dagger in this actor's hands is equivalent to a shield when it comes to parrying melee attacks, meaning she can use a dagger to parry weapons with the Overwhelming rule.</li>\n<li>II) Dismantler - When the actor uses their dagger to inflict a critical wound, that wound is automatically upgraded to a mortal wound.</li>\n<li>III) Destroyer - When the actor is already in a grapple at the beginning of her turn, her dagger attacks against the target she is grappling with ignore DR.</li>\n</ul>","purchaseCost":20,"tiered":true,"tiers":3,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PQOXcvkdea879m59"}},"_id":"EYjYOk3EEUAfmm9g"}
{"name":"Valorous","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/earth/strike-fist-stone-light.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is willing to hurl herself between an ally and a fatal blow. For any ally in close range, she can absorb the damage of any attack that would have reduced an ally to 0 or less HP. This is declared after the attack roll is made.</p>","purchaseCost":20,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KftnlScwdwYM97QT"}},"_id":"HGcAcwvP1DVzSH6V"}
{"name":"Mithril Curtain","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-deflect-teal.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor has a knack for avoiding the friendly fire. When the actor is caught in the blast radius of an attack, concoction, or spell that has an area of effect that originated from a friendly combatant (but not a foe trying to harm her), she can choose to avoid it outright.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.F0mok6utkcgt4B31"}},"_id":"HjrBvXrGyJmskGiU"}
{"name":"Bardique","type":"talent","img":"icons/tools/instruments/harp-yellow-teal.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is imbued with a form a magic that manifests through song, spoken word, dance, or some other type of performance art. This is a tiered talent that gets stronger every time it is purchased.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I) Revelry - The actor can give a performance that delights and inspires the party. During any non-violent scene (e.g. a visit to a tavern, a scene of court intrigue, etc.), she makes a challenging Performance skill check. For each hit, every member of her party restores 1 MP. When she uses this talent, it is no longer available to her until after the next session of downtime.</li>\n<li>II) Riot - The actor can give a performance that thrusts the party into a violent and rebellious fervor. During any violent scene (e.g. a battle against foes, a barroom brawl, etc.), she makes a challenging Performance skill check. For each hit, every member of her party may convert a single miss into a hit on their next roll. When she uses this talent, it is no longer available to her until after the next session of downtime.</li>\n<li>III) Rapture - The task difficulty of both Revelry and Riot is downgraded from challenging to trivial.</li>\n</ul>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":true,"tiers":3,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.o6cT0LkstPvzqOpH"}},"_id":"I4HwHrQaFRLiMJ6j"}
{"name":"Oracle","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/control/hypnosis-mesmerism-eye.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is highly susceptible to soma's hallucinatory effects and open-minded enough to seek insight and inspiration from these hallucinations. When she takes any form of soma immediately before making a Craft or Query roll, she may convert a single miss result into 1 hit.</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BX7lSM1TKZRifu8Q"}},"_id":"IPrJbyGhH2UEqpoY"}
{"name":"Blindside","type":"talent","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-white-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is adept at delivering brutal strikes that her target never see coming. She may burn 3 MP <em>before</em> making a melee or missile (but not magic) attack for the potential to do more damage. If her attack is successful, she makes a Stealth skill check with the same task difficulty as her attack roll and adds each hit to the damage.&nbsp;</p>","purchaseCost":30,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.R5jPSehkXQoo7GMP"}},"_id":"KQikro7kG50Ep1Ye"}
{"name":"Troll's Blood","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-shadow-red.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor&rsquo;s body repairs itself at an alarming rate. During downtime, she recovers a number of HP equal to her Endurance rank in <em>addition</em> to whatever else she decides to do with her time.&nbsp;</p>","purchaseCost":15,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Wqnqlkbexxrox8nB"}},"_id":"MmH4cSD6Pc1LLqbX"}
{"name":"Skill Push","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-flight-wings-runes-blue-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is especially good at a skill because her past has given her many opportunities to hone it to perfection. When making skill checks with this skill, you count every die result of 10 as 2 hits instead of 1. When selecting this talent, designate a single skill it applies to (e.g. Escape Artistry) and invent a past providing this advantage (e.g. Fugitive). Document this in the &ldquo;talents and spells&rdquo; section of the character sheet (e.g. &ldquo;Skill Push: Escape Artistry - Fugitive) but also fill in the &ldquo;10&rdquo; Talent Marker next to the appropriate skill. This talent may be selected multiple times.</p>\n<p>The &ldquo;past&rdquo; in this case can be a former career (e.g. priest), one&rsquo;s station in society (e.g. noble), a temporary set of circumstances (e.g. soma addict), or a formative experience (e.g. siege survivor). Here are some examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Unarmed Melee - Pit Fighter</li>\n<li>Performance - Mesmer</li>\n<li>Medicine - Court Physic</li>\n<li>Menace - Inquisitor</li>\n<li>Sleight of Hand - Waif</li>\n<li>Traps - Hunter</li>\n<li>Deception - Grifter</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It is also perfectly fine to reuse the same past for multiple Skill Pushes (e.g. Inquisitor can apply to both Menace and Query). While designating a Skill Push&rsquo;s past has no impact on game mechanics, it is something you can and should incorporate into the narrative.</p>\n<p>When selected for either Endurance or Willpower, the cost of this talent is doubled.</p>","purchaseCost":15,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Y7svabBrAHEigcXZ"}},"_id":"NJoXpKf6B0ihy7ra"}
{"name":"Deep Sleeper","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/control/sleep-bubble-purple.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor sleeps rather soundly for someone in their line of work. She restores +1 HP when she rests and +1 MP when she meditates.</p>","purchaseCost":5,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6rZeJswBTlW3a1pm"}},"_id":"O23ii7K9UM76cd1J"}
{"name":"Wardancer","type":"talent","img":"icons/magic/movement/abstract-ribbons-red-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<p>An actor is a particularly mobile and acrobatic combatant. During the enemy&rsquo;s turn, she can make an additional movement if she uses the dodge defense to completely evade an attack.</p>","purchaseCost":40,"tiered":false,"tiers":null,"currentTier":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"zER2pdCJ5klFAfnV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.95GAinmBp6Khl0a9"}},"_id":"O9ME1uKxhxcsuKJU"}
